Pre-Game Insights: Ghana commenced their 2026 World Cup qualifiers with a vital 1-0 win over Madagascar at the Baba Yara Stadium on Friday, November 17.
Comoros Islands beat the Central African Republic 4-2 in an entertaining encounter.
The Matchday two World Cup qualifier will take place at Moroni stadium – a multi-use stadium in Comoros that is currently used mostly for athletics competitions.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The two teams last met in the 2021 Africa Cup of Nations in Cameroon where Comoros beat Ghana 3-2 in a Group C encounter on January 19, 2023.
